# pyenv
#   For a library or binary, you may want to ignore these files
#   to allow collaborators to use their own python versions.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if you want to use it for your own purposes, uncomment:
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   poetry.lock
#   pyproject.toml is the main file for poetry, it should be committed.

# pdm
#   If pdm is used, it's recommended to commit pdm.lock and pyproject.toml
# .pdm-python
# .pdm-build/

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/frenzyryz/pip852
__pypackages__/

